00:13:17,909 --> 00:13:21,511
it turns out that most of those things, if you move them like 1% one way or the other,

299
00:13:21,511 --> 00:13:23,432
the universe lasts about 5 nanoseconds or something.

300
00:13:23,432 --> 00:13:27,374
So, that had the same problem where the combinations of sliders, you know,

301
00:13:27,374 --> 00:13:30,456
it was a very narrow range where you had an interesting kind of play experience.

302
00:13:30,456 --> 00:13:34,278
Diving a little bit deeper into the theories of the original life,

303
00:13:34,278 --> 00:13:36,919
one of the leading candidates is this thing called autocatalytic sets,

304
00:13:36,919 --> 00:13:39,621
which is roughly the chemistry over time will evolve.

305
00:13:40,092 --> 00:13:44,676
more and more elaborate, you know, chemicals in a given environment.

306
00:13:44,676 --> 00:13:46,277
We actually did prototypes of this,

307
00:13:46,277 --> 00:13:47,918
and to be honest, it wasn't very compelling.

308
00:13:47,918 --> 00:13:52,101
So we moved up a level to the cellular level

309
00:13:52,101 --> 00:13:55,124
and started looking into cellular processes and metabolism and stuff,

310
00:13:55,124 --> 00:13:57,365
and we did a pretty nice simulation of this,

311
00:13:57,365 --> 00:14:01,809
and again, you know, it just wasn't going to kind of reach the same numbers as the Sims,

312
00:14:01,809 --> 00:14:04,691
I thought.

313
00:14:04,691 --> 00:14:04,731
So...

314
00:14:05,276 --> 00:14:08,298
Another kind of intriguing theory is the pan-spermy theory,

315
00:14:08,298 --> 00:14:12,342
which is the fact that maybe life didn't start on Earth at all,

316
00:14:12,342 --> 00:14:14,063
but in fact came here from somewhere else,

317
00:14:14,063 --> 00:14:16,305
maybe an asteroid or a comet,

318
00:14:16,305 --> 00:14:17,346
landed on Earth.

319
00:14:17,346 --> 00:14:19,688
This is a rock we found, LH 84001.

320
00:14:20,133 --> 00:14:25,377
came from Mars, and we know that, you know, pretty well just by analyzing the chemical composition of it.

321
00:14:25,377 --> 00:14:29,299
And we found these little weird things on there that, you know, we've never seen before

322
00:14:29,299 --> 00:14:32,841
that looked like they could be, you know, maybe fossils of living organisms.

323
00:14:32,841 --> 00:14:35,483
The jury's still out on that. They probably aren't because they're so small.

324
00:14:35,483 --> 00:14:39,585
But still, the idea that material could have traveled from Mars to the Earth is pretty well known at this point.

325
00:14:39,585 --> 00:14:43,107
And there's a surprising amount of material, like when an asteroid hits the Earth,

326
00:14:43,107 --> 00:14:45,568
all little pieces of the Earth go out into orbit around the sun.

327
00:14:45,568 --> 00:14:48,590
Some of them will fall back in other planets, like Mars, for instance.

328
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:50,752
And so there's this idea of planetary crosstalk,

329
00:14:50,752 --> 00:14:53,294
that if there is life in a planetary system,

330
00:14:53,294 --> 00:14:55,536
chances are it will spread to other nearby planets,

331
00:14:55,536 --> 00:14:57,598
because it's a matter of tons per year

332
00:14:57,598 --> 00:15:00,140
that will fall, like in the early stages of this.

333
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:02,202
So there's a huge amount of crosstalk happening between the planets.

334
00:15:02,202 --> 00:15:05,364
And not only that, but it's looking more and more probable

335
00:15:05,364 --> 00:15:08,006
that there's the possibility of interstellar crosstalk,

336
00:15:08,006 --> 00:15:10,749
which is some of this material could actually travel to another star,

337
00:15:10,749 --> 00:15:15,493
because some of these bacteria can last for millions of years in a desiccated form,

338
00:15:15,493 --> 00:15:17,074
and they're very radiation resistant.

339
00:15:17,572 --> 00:15:19,494
So, we'll get back to this a little bit later.

340
00:15:19,494 --> 00:15:23,098
There's actually, now what I'm talking about so far is undirected panspermia.

341
00:15:23,098 --> 00:15:25,300
There's this other idea of directed panspermia,

342
00:15:25,300 --> 00:15:28,023
and in fact a society I found that is promoting this,

343
00:15:28,023 --> 00:15:30,545
that let's start sending spores out into space

344
00:15:30,545 --> 00:15:33,789
and, you know, five million years from now they might land somewhere

345
00:15:33,789 --> 00:15:35,351
and start, you know, growing on another planet.

346
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:38,754
And it's cool that people think that far ahead, you know.

347
00:15:38,754 --> 00:15:39,815
Okay, back to the research side.

