00:29:28,070 --> 00:29:31,292
And I've had really good luck with interns.

682
00:29:31,292 --> 00:29:34,794
Generally, the balance I'm trying to strive for on a team now is about one-third veteran,

683
00:29:34,794 --> 00:29:37,915
one-third kind of intern is young blood, and one-third mid-level.

684
00:29:37,915 --> 00:29:40,137
And that seems like a really good kind of chemistry on the team.

685
00:29:40,877 --> 00:29:46,339
A typical thing is that we have a lot of people coming in, we're trying to filter for hiring,

686
00:29:46,339 --> 00:29:51,081
is we have thousands of resumes. The HR people don't quite know exactly what we're looking

687
00:29:51,081 --> 00:29:54,022
for because they're not experts in the field. They try their best and sort and give us a

688
00:29:54,022 --> 00:29:58,044
pile of resumes and we kind of choose from those. And it's a very ineffective filter

689
00:29:58,044 --> 00:30:02,306
in a lot of cases. You know, what I'm finding is a much more effective filter is a few programs

690
00:30:02,306 --> 00:30:04,867
in these universities that are teaching, you know, interactive design now.

691
00:30:05,127 --> 00:30:07,748
We have a few students come in and do very well in those programs.

